¶ ⦊
  ‖ We can identify the origin with the complex number $(0,0) =
    0 ∈ 𝗖$. ⦉

  ‖ For this reason we call $0 ∈ 𝗖$ the ❬complex origin❭. ⦉

  ‖ Likewise, the imaginary number $(0, 1) = i ∈ 𝗖$ corresponds
    to $(0,1)$ ⦉

  ‖ Clearly, the horizontal axis corresponds to the purely real
    numbers and the vertical axis corresponds to the purely
    imaginary numbers. ⦉

  ‖ For these reasons, we refer to these axes as the ❬real
    axis❭ and ❬imaginary axis❭, respectively. ⦉

  ‖ We refer to the above figure as the ❬complex plane❭ (or
    ❬Argand diagram❭). ⦉
⦉

